  "body": "### Description\nAs a Besu dev, I want to establish a baseline for peering behavior so that when we make changes to peering code, we know whether we are making it better. \n\n### Acceptance Criteria\neg Release 22.1.2 is a good opportunity to observe the behaviour of new nodes as they start up - eg how long it takes a new besu node to sync goerli. - make a doc to paint a picture of what normal looks like for each testnet/mainnet. Screenshots if helpful\nExample of what may be helpful to track:\n* Time to sync from scratch (where appropriate)\n* Time for an existing node to catch up\n* Time to gain N peers\n\n",
